parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power windows can cause inconvenience, discomfort, and potentially lead to accidents if the driver is distracted while trying to operate the windows.
symptoms: Power windows do not work
power windows stick
power windows do not return to their normal position
power windows have a delayed return to their normal position
power windows have a sudden loss of pressure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the windshield wipers can cause reduced visibility, leading to accidents, especially during rainy or snowy weather conditions.
symptoms: Windshield wipers do not work
windshield wipers work intermittently
windshield wipers stop working while driving
windshield wipers come on and off without being activated
windshield wipers do not return to their normal position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the windshield wiper circuit board can cause the windshield wipers to malfunction, leading to reduced visibility and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: Windshield wipers work intermittently
windshield wipers stop working
windshield wipers come on and off without being activated
windshield wipers do not return to their normal position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the hydraulic system can cause the power windows and other components to malfunction, leading to inconvenience, discomfort, and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: Power windows do not work
power windows stick
power windows do not return to their normal position
power windows have a delayed return to their normal position
power windows have a sudden loss of pressure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the torsion bar can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities. It can also result in sudden stops, loss of steering, and damage to other vehicle components.
symptoms: The vehicle's front end collapses
the tire rubs against the fender
the vehicle pulls to one side
the vehicle wanders all over the road
excessive effort is required to maintain control
loud noises or banging sounds are heard
and the vehicle's suspension fails intermittently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent failure of the ABS system can cause extended stopping distances, loss of vehicle control, and accidents, leading to potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The ABS light illuminates
the brake pedal goes to the floor
the vehicle pulls to one side while braking
the brakes fail to engage
the brakes release at times
the vehicle has a mushy pedal
and the brakes make a noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Pedal Goes to the Floor
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: When the brake pedal goes to the floor, the vehicle may not stop, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal goes to the floor
the vehicle has extended stopping distances
and the brakes fail to engage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unequal voltage in ABS sensors can cause the ABS system to malfunction, leading to extended stopping distances, loss of vehicle control, and accidents.
symptoms: The ABS light illuminates
the vehicle has a delayed stop-time
and the brakes fail to engage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A brake line rupture can cause a total loss of brakes, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal goes to the floor
and the vehicle has extended stopping distances.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A stuck accelerator pedal can cause the vehicle to accelerate unexpectedly, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly accelerates
the brakes burn and catch on fire
and the vehicle does not stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake caliper failure can cause the vehicle to pull to one side while braking, leading to loss of vehicle control and accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle pulls to one side while braking
and the brake pedal makes a popping noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Overloading a vehicle can affect its braking capacity, leading to extended stopping distances and accidents.
symptoms: The brakes squeal and fade
and the vehicle has a lack of adequate brakes.
